haken (120 rpm) at 37 \u00b0C in a humidified 5% CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2 <\/span><span>atmosphere. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042377,"guid":"2B03F77002F711EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042370,"previous_guid":"F5C6A9E002F611EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4CAC293D05C044DAB84E3771F007BDB9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"16F0731C748A48FF83700AC3AEED286A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Determination of total and viable cell numbers was performed with Vi-Cell XR Cell Viability Analyzer (Beckman Coulter, Fullerton, CA, USA) and CellProfiler software. The images obtained from Vi-Cell XR were analyzed and total and viable cell numbers were counted using the CellProfiler pipeline. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042379,"guid":"8302363002F711EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042377,"previous_guid":"2B03F77002F711EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A73A07B9564244DDAB7DE50F3B9AD78B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4D780DA865914C598DA4A0CF49B96FC2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Harvesting samples <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">To isolate RNA that accurately reflects the transcriptome at the point of harvest, cells should be processed by lysing and homogenizing in RNA lysis buffer containing guanidine thiocyanate (buffer RLT, RNA lysis buffer, QIAGEN) as soon as possible (within 15 minutes, if possible).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":[{"id":12,"title":"Critical step","icon":"CriticalIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042380,"guid":"9225F1B002F711EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042379,"previous_guid":"8302363002F711EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3220128AFA7C47D7998185D9F1343E9F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7B18732AB7FB43359ADD6AE5B2B21BBF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The medium containing the suspended CHO cells (400,000 cells) was transferred from the cell culture flask to 1.5 mL centrifuge tubes. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042389,"guid":"073D009002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042380,"previous_guid":"9225F1B002F711EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6D80D51B0E7641C1B88E5C7591368C00","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E9BFD768DF124EDB9295614FB8B665B0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Each centrifuge tube was centrifuged for 5 min at 300 \u00d7<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">g<\/span><span> and all supernatant was removed. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042390,"guid":"08892FA002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042389,"previous_guid":"073D009002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C9D56BFAD4A242238954469CBE7C8FF9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"87C549E3813E4807A962AB21136B7559","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">An aliquot of 200 \u00b5L of Gibco PBS (1\u00d7, calcium and magnesium-free, pH 7.2; Thermo Fisher Scientific) was added to the cell pellet and pipetted up and down five times to resuspend thoroughly. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042396,"guid":"3FF1256002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042390,"previous_guid":"08892FA002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"417283A9BE5C472BA74B83AABD41CA74","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"16DF49CD5F204E71A08D82263A287DD5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The centrifuge tube was centrifuged for 5 min at 300 \u00d7<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">g<\/span><span> and all supernatant was removed. The centrifuge tube was flicked to loosen the cell pellet from the bottom. <\/span><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042397,"guid":"496B723002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042396,"previous_guid":"3FF1256002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"46531AEFA46B47EAA425139FFE1ACCE9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"831E2AE4D86B439B83D171A74CA5E565","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">An aliquot of 350 \u00b5L of the buffer RLT (RNA lysis buffer; QIAGEN), which contains containing guanidine thiocyanate, was added to the pellet and pipetted up and down five times to mix thoroughly.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042409,"guid":"BDE2421002FF11EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042397,"previous_guid":"496B723002FA11EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"DE74170C20EF4ECFBEF492258C68D56D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F8F7F62193CB485E8D8444FE5BEF8708","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The entire cell suspension was immediately loaded onto a QIAshredder spin column (QIAGEN) and homogenized by centrifugation for 2 min in a microcentrifuge at maximum speed. The resultant homogenized lysate was kept at \u221280 \u00b0C until RNA extraction.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042410,"guid":"D4624C6002FF11EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042409,"previous_guid":"BDE2421002FF11EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B81206902A664ABCA5167F5650D35987","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"1ED91F9C5DEC4D4BB8D045198305696B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">RNA isolation, cDNA library construction, and RNA-Seq<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042411,"guid":"08904CD0030011EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042410,"previous_guid":"D4624C6002FF11EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1E19BB2EAE5C41B3933F62ABAEF34722","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"22FEBB8CF96F472ABF621BB928236046","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Total RNA isolation was performed using an RNeasy mini kit (QIAGEN) according to the manufacturer's protocol.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1042412,"guid":"DCE30180030011EBB7C14BB565180390","previous_id":1042411,"previous_guid":"08904CD0030011EBB7C14BB565180390","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"489261EB782F477A80528E1353F365BE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4E35A299234E420ABD02E275484E9C2E","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The quality of total RNA was assessed by RIN values using the Agilent 2200 TapeStation (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA, USA) and sequenced on an Illumina NextSeq 500 platform with 75-bp single-end reads according to the manufacturer's protocol.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":"","materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol is for RNA Isolation from suspended Chinese hamster ovary (CHO) cells. Wash cells once in 1\u00d7 PBS and isolate RNA using Qiashredder columns and the RNeasy mini kit. In the case of RNA-Seq, which reveals the presence and quantity of RNA in a biological sample at any moment, it is necessary to consider that gene expression responds over a short time interval (several seconds to a few minutes) in many organisms. Therefore, to isolate RNA that accurately reflects the transcriptome at the point of harvest, raw biological samples should be processed by lysing and homogenizing in RNA lysis buffer containing guanidine thiocyanate (buffer RLT, RNA lysis buffer, QIAGEN) as soon as possible (within 15 minutes, if possible).<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1617439059}